3. Realization Mapping from Governing Artifacts
3.1 Website Specification to Technical Realization
The Website Specification defines what the website must do. Technical realization must therefore implement required page and view behaviors, CMS-managed generation of detail pages where specified, inquiry flow and lifecycle where specified, accessibility behavior, responsive behavior, metadata and discoverability behavior, and acceptance-relevant operational behavior.
Technical implementation must not reinterpret these requirements as optional merely because the selected stack makes them inconvenient.
3.2 Configuration Artifacts to Runtime Configuration
The Site Configuration Standard defines the governed configuration model. The Site Configuration Record defines the active values for this implementation.
Technical realization must therefore define where governed configuration values are stored or retrieved at runtime, how they are resolved into consumable runtime structures, where they are injected, which technical consumers may access them, and which technical consumers may not bypass the approved configuration pathway.
3.3 Solution Architecture Standard to Technical Realization
The Website Solution Architecture Standard defines the logical module system and structural rules.
Technical realization must therefore map each logical module to one or more technical realization targets, each dependency rule to an implementation boundary, each orthogonality rule to a technical separation of concern, and each invariant to a preserved runtime or codebase boundary.
3.4 Realization and Page Composition Standard to Implementation Realization
The Website Realization and Page Composition Standard defines buildable modules, reusable components, page types, page instances, page composition rules, and CMS-managed versus fixed aspects.
Technical realization must therefore define how buildable modules are implemented, how reusable components are implemented, how page types are represented, how page instances are created and resolved, how page composition is performed, and how editor-approved variation is technically enforced without permitting structural invention.
